{
  "texts": [
    "This reduction further improves to 63% for space missions.",
    "However, this approach introduces a noticeable bias in r, even though it remains within 1σ.",
    "We introduce an alternative approach (L2), where we parameterize the fraction (C res l /C lens l) as A L instead of f dl and estimate N del l based on simulations.",
    "This method reduces biases by 88% for the gSAT+gLAT experiment and by 71% for the satellite experiment, with almost the same σ(r).",
    "A more promising method (L3) is to add the lensing template B-mode as an additional frequency channel, which leads to negligible bias on r in both experiments with a compatible uncertainty reduction performance."
  ]
}